HEADWORD: Pis
<hw>Pi`s⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>pis⟦eacute⟧</ets>, from <ets>piser</ets> to stamp, pound, L.
<ets>pisare</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Arch.)</fld> <def>A species of wall made
of stiff earth or clay rammed in between molds which are carried up as
the wall rises; -- called also <altname>pis⟦eacute⟧
